gtsoft.ivory.server.jca.cci
Class IvoryInteractionSpec

java.lang.Object
  gtsoft.ivory.server.jca.cci.IvoryInteractionSpec
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable, javax.resource.cci.InteractionSpec
public class IvoryInteractionSpec
extends java.lang.Object
implements javax.resource.cci.InteractionSpec

Use an IvoryInteractionSpec object as the first parameter to Interaction.execute. IvoryInteractionSpec holds all necessary control information for the Ivory resource adapter to execute a request.

getEndpoint

public java.lang.String getEndpoint()
Get the endpoint for the request. The endpoint value is extremely important as it controls which Ivory project is executed. The format of the endpoint is a directory structure where the Ivory project was deployed to. For example, if an Ivory project was deployed to /var/ivory/IvoryWebServices/soap/cics/acctmain the value of the endpoint would be "/soap/cics/acctmain".

Returns:
the endpoint of the Ivory project to be executed

For example, if an Ivory project was deployed to /var/ivory/IvoryWebServices/soap/cics/acctmain the value of the endpoint would be "/soap/cics/acctmain".

Parameters:

isExchangeSOAPData

public boolean isExchangeSOAPData()
Returns true if your application is exchanging SOAP style data. This means the root element of the request is a SOAP envelope which would contain a SOAP body and optionally SOAP headers.

Returns:
true, SOAP data is being exchanged, false the data does not contain SOAP wrapper elements. The default is false.

setExchangeSOAPData

public void setExchangeSOAPData(boolean inExchangeSOAPData)
Set true if your application is exchanging SOAP style data. This means the root element of the request is a SOAP envelope which would contain a SOAP body and optionally SOAP headers.

Parameters:
inExchangeSOAPData - true, SOAP data is being exchanged, false the data does not contain SOAP wrapper elements. If this method is not called the default value is false.
